	<div class=3D"fl-module-content fl-node-content">
		<h1 class=3D"fl-heading">
		<span class=3D"fl-heading-text">Soil Salinity and Sodicity</span>
	</h1>
	</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
	</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"fl-row fl-row-full-width fl-row-bg-none fl-node-afpiqty8rg7l =
fl-row-default-height fl-row-align-center" data-node=3D"afpiqty8rg7l">
	<div class=3D"fl-row-content-wrap">
		<div class=3D"uabb-row-separator uabb-top-row-separator">
</div>
						<div class=3D"fl-row-content fl-row-fixed-width fl-node-content">
	=09
<div class=3D"fl-col-group fl-node-hbm9oqe67nay" data-node=3D"hbm9oqe67nay"=
>
			<div class=3D"fl-col fl-node-vaqmc23jkyhu fl-col-bg-color fl-col-small f=
l-col-small-full-width" data-node=3D"vaqmc23jkyhu">
	<div class=3D"fl-col-content fl-node-content"><div class=3D"fl-module fl-m=
odule-rich-text fl-node-v4obtcus305f" data-node=3D"v4obtcus305f">
	<div class=3D"fl-module-content fl-node-content">
		<div class=3D"fl-rich-text">
	<p style=3D"text-align: left;">Soil salinization occurs as salts (e.g. cal=
cium, potassium, magnesium) accumulate in the soil, particularly in irrigat=
ed regions with low rainfall and high evapotranspiration. Similarly, soil s=
odicity refers to high sodium (Na) levels in soil. These conditions can cau=
se plant moisture stress as roots have trouble taking up water from the soi=
l. High sodium levels cause soil particles to disperse, clogging soil pores=
 and exacerbating issues with erosion.</p>
<p style=3D"text-align: left;">There are three types of salt-affected soils=
:</p>
<ol style=3D"text-align: left;">
<li>Saline soils contain high concentrations of soluble salts. Soluble salt=
s present in the root zone can make it difficult for plants to extract wate=
r from the soil.</li>
<li>Sodic soils have too much sodium.</li>
<li>Saline-sodic soils have too much sodium and other soluble salts.</li>
</ol>
</div>
	</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
			<div class=3D"fl-col fl-node-n9fuj5eh7xs3 fl-col-bg-color fl-col-small f=
l-col-small-full-width" data-node=3D"n9fuj5eh7xs3">
	<div class=3D"fl-col-content fl-node-content"><div class=3D"fl-module fl-m=
odule-photo fl-node-ym3z2vugsk8r" data-node=3D"ym3z2vugsk8r">
	<div class=3D"fl-module-content fl-node-content">
		<div class=3D"fl-photo fl-photo-align-center" itemscope=3D"" itemtype=3D"=
https://schema.org/ImageObject">
	<div class=3D"fl-photo-content fl-photo-img-jpg">
				<img fetchpriority=3D"high" decoding=3D"async" class=3D"fl-photo-img wp=
-image-96 size-full no-lazyload" src=3D"https://washingtonsoilhealthinitiat=
ive.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Salinization-1-DGL-scaled.jpg" alt=3D"A =
field with intruding water." itemprop=3D"image" height=3D"1080" width=3D"19=
20" title=3D"Salinization 1 (DGL)">
					</div>
		<div class=3D"fl-photo-caption fl-photo-caption-below" itemprop=3D"captio=
n">Soils with excessive salts can create soil sealing which restricts water=
 infiltration.=20
Photo credit: Deirdre Griffin LaHue</div>
	</div>
	</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
	</div>

<div class=3D"fl-col-group fl-node-0b573sx1jkqi" data-node=3D"0b573sx1jkqi"=
>
			<div class=3D"fl-col fl-node-d0me1gac7ol5 fl-col-bg-color" data-node=3D"=
d0me1gac7ol5">
	<div class=3D"fl-col-content fl-node-content"><div class=3D"fl-module fl-m=
odule-rich-text fl-node-3jgx5ybkhst1" data-node=3D"3jgx5ybkhst1">
	<div class=3D"fl-module-content fl-node-content">
		<div class=3D"fl-rich-text">
	<h2 style=3D"text-align: left;">Management practices differ for saline, so=
dic and saline-sodic soils:</h2>
<ul style=3D"text-align: left;">
<li>Saline soils are reclaimed by leaching salts below the root zone with t=
he application of low-salt irrigation water. Plants are most susceptible to=
 soil salinity at germination. In some cases, moving salt away from the ger=
minating seed is all that is necessary.</li>
<li>Sodic soils require the addition of soluble calcium, followed by leachi=
ng of sodium. Calcium promotes soil aggregation. Gypsum is the most common =
material used to supply calcium for sodic soil reclamation. Elemental S is =
useful for sodic soil reclamation only when the soil contains free lime.</l=
i>
<li>Saline-sodic soils must be treated for sodicity first. These soils firs=
t require calcium additions to correct sodium, followed by leaching to remo=
ve salts.</li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"text-align: left;">When developing a plan for salt management, =
keep in mind these concepts:</p>
<ul style=3D"text-align: left;">
<li>Irrigation water can create or worsen salt-affected soil conditions, ma=
king irrigation water management important. Test your irrigation water for =
salt before using.</li>
<li>Some crops are more sensitive to salts than others, and plant sensitivi=
ty varies depending on crop growth stage and weather.</li>
<li>High concentrations of chloride and boron can reduce crop yield indepen=
dent of saline or sodic soil conditions.</li>
<li>Reclamation of salt-affected soils requires adequate drainage. If neces=
sary, improve drainage before attempting reclamation.</li>
</ul>
</div>
	</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
	</div>

